#: data/levels/world2/scripts_corrupted_cutscene.txt:2
msgid "Never had Tux been missing sunlight more than ever before."
msgstr "Aldri før hadde Tux sakna sollys meir."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_corrupted_cutscene.txt:3
msgid ""
"Since the rain had stopped and the sky was clear, Tux hoped to have found a "
"nice, safe place to take a short break."
msgstr "Sidan det hadde slutta å regna og himmelen var skyfri, håpa Tux han no hadde funne ein trygg og triveleg stad å ta ein rast."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_corrupted_cutscene.txt:4
msgid ""
"Just as he was about to rest, the sudden sound of rustling leaves from a "
"bush nearby startled Tux."
msgstr "Men nett då han skulle til å ta ein pust i bakken, kvakk han til av rørsler i nokre buskar."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_corrupted_cutscene.txt:5
msgid ""
"He went to investigate and got startled by a Vicious Ivy, tumbling out of "
"the bushes!"
msgstr "Han gjekk for å undersøka nærare, men vart overrumpla av ein giftig eføy som hoppa fram!"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_corrupted_cutscene.txt:6
msgid ""
"However, this one looked different. Its usual bright green leaves seemed to "
"have turned an ailing purple."
msgstr "Og eføyen såg litt rar ut. Han hadde inntørka lilla blad i staden for friske grøne."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_corrupted_cutscene.txt:7
msgid ""
"Before Tux even had the chance to think about what had happened to the poor "
"thing, the ground began to shake violently..."
msgstr "Men før Tux fekk tid til å undra seg over kva som hadde hendt den stakkars planta, starta bakken under han å skjelva ..."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_corrupted_cutscene.txt:8
msgid ""
"Massive purple roots burst through the ground, followed by an onslaught of "
"many more coming closer and closer!"
msgstr "Kraftige lilla røter sprengde seg gjennom jordskorpa - og dei kom nærmare og nærmare!"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_corrupted_cutscene.txt:9
msgid ""
"Tux panicked! Whatever these roots were, they were covering everything. "
"Where could he go?"
msgstr "Tux fekk panikk! Røtene - eller kva det no var - dekte snart alt. Kor kunne han flykta?"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_corrupted_cutscene.txt:10
msgid ""
"But he cannot give up now! Tux could not leave her behind. Not in a place "
"being overrun by these violent roots."
msgstr "Men han måtte ikkje gje opp! Han kunne jo ikkje etterlata Penny her, omringa av valdelege røter."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_corrupted_cutscene.txt:11
msgid "He must rescue Penny! He must get to that tower!"
msgstr "Han måtte redda ho! Han måtte komma seg til tårnet!"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_default.txt:2
msgid "---Insert Cutscene Here---"
msgstr "---Set inn animasjonssekvens her---"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:2
msgid ""
"Despite the Ghost Tree's defeat and a sliver of life returning to the once "
"lush forest, the land was still in shambles."
msgstr "Spøkjelsetreet var knust, og det var no ein kime til liv i den før så frodige skogen, men landskapet var framleis nesten fullstendig utarma."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:3
msgid ""
"The ground was riddled with cracks and crevices. And now one of them was "
"blocking Tux's path..."
msgstr "Bakken var full av sprekker og kløfter. Og ei av kløftene sperra no vegen vidare for Tux ..."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:4
msgid ""
"Fortunately for him, a Granito, alive and well, revealed themself, excited "
"to see him on the other side of the crevice."
msgstr "Men på hi side av kløfta stod det ein granito i beste velgåande og vinka til Tux."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:5
msgid ""
"The Granito spoke of 3 groups of his fellow Granito who had gotten lost when"
" trying to escape the roots to the east coast."
msgstr "Han fortalde om tre grupper med granitoar som hadde fare vill medan dei prøvde å flykta mot austkysten, vekk frå røtene."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:6
msgid ""
"They were swallowed by the earth as the ground collapsed in on itself. If "
"Tux could help find them they could help him reach the other side."
msgstr "Dei vart fanga når jorda rasa saman rundt dei. Viss Tux kunne få granitoane fri, kunne dei hjelpa han over kløfta."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:7
msgid ""
"Tux agreed to help! Soon after he noticed a dying roots revealing a path "
"underneath, he began his search for the lost Granito."
msgstr "Sjølvsagt ville Tux hjelpa! Han oppdaga ein sti under ei rotnande rot og gav seg i veg på leit etter granitoane."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:8
msgid ""
"With the help of the saved Granito, Tux managed to reach the other side."
msgstr "Med hjelp frå granitoane kom Tux seg over kløfta."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:9
msgid ""
"He was glad there were more Granito that had survived the Ghost Tree's "
"overgrowth."
msgstr "Han vart glad då han såg at det der var fleire granitoar som hadde overlevd herjingane til spøkjelsestreet."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:10
msgid ""
"One of the Granito asked him what a penguin like him was doing so far from "
"the Antarctic."
msgstr "Ein av granitoane spurde kva ein pingvin som han gjorde så langt frå Sørpolen."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:11
msgid ""
"Tux replied that he was looking for his friend Penny and that she was "
"captured by an evil creature named \"Nolok\". A name the Granito remembered "
"unpleasantly..."
msgstr "Tux fortalde at han leita etter venninna si Penny, som var teken til fange av ein ufyseleg fyr med namn Nolok. Namnet fekk granitoane til å grøssa ..."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:12
msgid ""
"The Granito mentioned they knew his homeland. But whether he still called it"
" his home nor if he held Penny there, they do not know for certain."
msgstr "Dei sa at dei kjende til heimlandet til Nolok. Men om han framleis heldt til der eller hadde ført Penny dit, var dei ikkje sikre på."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:13
msgid ""
"They offered to show Tux the way. It was the least they could do to show "
"their gratitute."
msgstr "Dei kunne uansett visa Tux vegen. Dei var så takksame for hjelpa, så det var det minste dei kunne gjera!"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:14
msgid ""
"Tux gladly accepted and together with a handful of Granito they soon made "
"their way to the tropics, in the north-east."
msgstr "Tux tok imot tilbodet, og han og ei handfull granitoar la i veg nordaust, mot tropane."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:15
msgid ""
"The remaining Granito would stay behind, slowly rebuilding their home, now "
"that the corruption was finally vanquished..."
msgstr "Resten av granitoane vart verande for å byggja opp att heimlandet, no som rota til ròtenskapen var rydda av vegen ..."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:16
#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:17
#: data/levels/world2/scripts_floral_blossom.txt:18
msgid "Granito freed!"
msgstr "Granitoar sette fri!"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_forest_intro.txt:2
msgid "After quite the long trip, Tux arrived at the new biome."
msgstr "Etter ein lang seglas gjekk Tux i land på ei ny øy, med eit heilt anna klima."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_forest_intro.txt:3
msgid ""
"Tux was astonished by the scale of this colorful land which was quite "
"different from his home."
msgstr "Han vart overvelda over dette vidstrekte, fargerike landskapet som var så annleis enn heimtraktene hans."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_forest_intro.txt:4
msgid "But how was he ever going to find Nolok in this vast forest?"
msgstr "Men korleis kunne han finna Nolok i denne enorme skogen?"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_forest_intro.txt:5
msgid ""
"Tux thought for a moment and decided to find a place high up to get a better"
" view."
msgstr "Han tenkte seg litt om og gav seg så i leit etter eit utkikkspunkt der han lettare kunne få oversikt."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_forest_intro.txt:6
msgid ""
"Maybe he could find some kind of landmark to help him locate Nolok, wherever"
" he may be."
msgstr "Kanskje han kunne finna eit landemerke å navigera etter i jakta på Nolok, kor no enn han var?"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttree_cutscene.txt:2
msgid ""
"High on the very top of the dilapidated tower, once again Tux found... "
"nothing."
msgstr "Frå toppen av det falleferdige tårnet såg Tux igjen - ingenting."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttree_cutscene.txt:3
msgid ""
"He could not believe it. He was shocked. Confused. Was this not where he "
"needed to go?"
msgstr "Han kunne ikkje tru det. Han var sjokkert. Forvirra. Hadde han gått feil?"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttree_cutscene.txt:4
msgid "Did Nolok's hints trick him afterall? Did he walk into a trap?"
msgstr "Hadde Nolok likevel klart å lura han? Var han narra i ei felle?"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttree_cutscene.txt:5
msgid ""
"Tux had not long to think about all this, the tower began shaking violetly. "
"His assumption prove correct instantly."
msgstr "Men han fekk ikkje lang tid til å tenkja over dette. Tårnet starta å rista. Ja, det var nok ei felle!"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttree_cutscene.txt:6
msgid ""
"He made it! He escaped the collapsing tower just in time as the structure "
"now fully gave in. But the roots were not done yet!"
msgstr "Han greidde det! Nett før tårnet fall saman, klarte han å hoppa ut. Men røtene var enno ikkje ferdige med han!"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttree_cutscene.txt:7
msgid ""
"This was only the beginning, as he had found the root of the problem... "
"towering over the small penguin."
msgstr "Dette var berre starten. Han hadde funne rota til alle problema ... Og det tårna seg no over den vesle pingvinen."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttree_cutscene.txt:8
msgid ""
"Tux watched in shock as the roots dug through the tower's walls, faster and "
"faster. He had to get out of there, fast!"
msgstr "Tux såg i vantru på at røtene grov seg gjennom tårnmuren. Han måtte komma seg ut, og det fort!"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttree_cutscene.txt:9
msgid ""
"The roots were now everywhere. The tower become more unstable by the second."
" Slowly, it collapsed in on itself."
msgstr "Røtene var no overalt. Tårnet vart stadig meir ustabilt. Snart ville det rasa saman."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttree_cutscene.txt:10
msgid ""
"Tux ran as fast as he could, but the roots would not let him leave as they "
"blocked off the only path to the main entrance."
msgstr "Tux sprang alt det føtene bar, men røtene hadde ikkje tenkt å la han sleppa unna; dei blokkerte den einaste vegen til utgangen."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttree_cutscene.txt:11
msgid ""
"Across the hallway, on the other side, there was a huge crack in the wall. "
"Tux saw himself forced to take the leap of faith, if he wished to not be "
"crushed."
msgstr "Men på andre sida av rommet var det ein stor sprekk i muren. Om han ikkje ville verta knust, var han nøydd til å ta sjansen ..."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttreewin_cutscene.txt:2
msgid "Was it over? Was the nightmare finally over?"
msgstr "Var det slutt? Var marerittet endeleg over?"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttreewin_cutscene.txt:3
msgid ""
"Tux could not believe his eyes, but it seemed so! The roots began "
"retreating. The ground looked more vital again."
msgstr "Tux kunne knapt tru det, men det såg slik ut! Røtene starta å trekkja seg tilbake. Bakken såg meir livskraftig ut."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttreewin_cutscene.txt:4
msgid ""
"Though as much as he was ecstatic about seeing the land restored and "
"beginning to heal... where to now?"
msgstr "Han var sjølvsagt overlukkeleg over å sjå landskapet komma til live igjen, men kor skulle han no dra?"

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttreewin_cutscene.txt:5
msgid ""
"The forest, the tower... those were the only leads Tux had. He had no clue "
"where Nolok could be hiding, if he even was here to begin with. Or rather "
"anymore."
msgstr "Skogen, tårnet ... Det var dei einaste leietrådane han hadde. Han ante ikkje kor Nolok gøymde seg, eller om han enno var her."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttreewin_cutscene.txt:6
msgid ""
"There was no one around Tux could ask for help. All but the remains of "
"corrupted husks littered the ground as he moved along in thought. No living "
"creature in sight."
msgstr "Det var ingen Tux kunne spørja om hjelp. Berre dei ròtne restane av røtene låg att på bakken. Ikkje eit levande vesen å sjå."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttreewin_cutscene.txt:7
msgid ""
"Hoping to discover some kind of clue - anything! - Tux's best bet was to "
"continue exploring this side of the forest, as destroyed as it may be."
msgstr "Han håpte å finna ein leietråd. Kva som helst! Den var nok lurast å utforska resten av skogen, sjølv om han var nesten øydelagd."

#: data/levels/world2/scripts_ghosttreewin_cutscene.txt:8
msgid ""
"There must be something, somewhere, able to help him to find Nolok! "
"Right...?"
msgstr "Det måtte vel vera noko der som kunne setja han på sporet av Nolok! Eller ...?"

